<br>
While grouped with a caster and a few others a couple of days ago our group got a pull of 3 sarnaks. Our caster (luckily not our only healer) decided in his infinite wisdom to dish out some melee damage. Of course he immediately started taking punishment. With his hit points down to less then one red cell I told him to back up. He did and the sarnaks turned to attack me (we were directly across from each other). Now here's where irony takes over. As he steps back he casts a spell which he thinks makes him invisible (although he never disappeared from my sight). Then in group speak he said &quot;Look guys they can't see me. Hahaha.&quot; and takes a step toward the sarnaks. At the same time he steps forward the sarnaks turn and take him down with one hit! The timing couldn't have been more perfect. When the fight was over I couldn't help but laugh as I saw him curled in the fetal position on the ground. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utranthas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tranthas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 2:21:45 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave It To A Caster</span><hr size=1> Famous last words.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey guys, watch this!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/16/01 3:07:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Leave It To A Caster</span><hr size=1> This reminds me a bit of a famous incedent in the US Civil War.  A Union General and his troops were under fire from some Confedarates, who were about 800 or 1000 yards away. His troops were taking cover instead of moving as he had ordered them.  So, in a show of &quot;follow me&quot; leadership, he surmounted a small rise and called out to his troops:<br>
<br>
&quot;Come on! Move!  At this distance they couldn't hit the broad side of a &lt;URK&gt;&quot;<br>
<br>
and he was shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=749.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=782.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.emailToFriend?topicID=760.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.threadControl?topicID=760.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=760.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=760.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafehouselaboratory">Laboratory<option value="thesafehousefrm15"